---
description: "NestJS HTTP conventions"
globs:
  - "backend/src/**/*.controller.ts"
  - "backend/src/**/*.module.ts"
  - "backend/src/**/dto/**/*.ts"
  - "backend/src/**/*.dto.ts"
  - "backend/src/**/*.guard.ts"
  - "backend/src/**/*.interceptor.ts"
  - "backend/src/**/*.filter.ts"
alwaysApply: false
---

# Backend Nest HTTP

- Keep controllers thin: validate input, delegate to services, and format responses.
- Put all complex business logic in services, helpers, or domain modules, never controllers.
- Validate request bodies with DTOs/class-validator and transform with class-transformer decorators.
- Return status codes and envelopes consistent with existing APIs (JSON `{ data, meta }` or equivalent).
- Group related providers/exports inside feature modules; avoid mixing unrelated providers.
